⁣⁣Many people often feel “jealous” of other’s success. Jealousy arises when you fear that you can’t create the same results for yourself.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Realize that seeing someone else become successful is more proof that you can also be successful! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
When you view it from this lens, all jealousy disappears. All jealousy is, is fear and doubt about your OWN power.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The next time you feel jealousy when you see someone manifest what you want, ask yourself: “Why am I afraid that I can’t accomplish this?”, “What work do I need to do in order to feel more confident in my own manifesting skills and abilities?”, “What is this triggering in me that I need to address?”. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
When we ask better questions, we can find solutions.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It’s never about someone else. It’s always about you. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Get to the root of your feelings and you will find that the jealousy will dissipate. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The happier you are for others, the sooner you can bring that into your life.⁣⁣ 

⁣⁣The next time you see someone manifest what you want, get excited! That’s even more proof that it can happen for you.🙏🏻✨⁣⁣

Worrying and stressing does more harm than good. ⁣
⁣
When you worry, you are giving your attention to what you DON’T want to happen - that’s all you are doing.⁣
⁣
It takes the same energy to worry OR have belief in something.⁣
⁣
Remember..Your ego needs to constantly be doing something or solving a problem - hence why we worry so much.⁣
⁣
Worrying is NOT action. It’s just energy you are directing to what you don’t want to happen.⁣
⁣
Your mind will run wild if you let it. Decide to change the narrative.⁣
⁣
The next time you worry, pause and ask yourself:⁣
⁣
“What do I actually want in this moment?” ⁣
“What if things worked out?”⁣
“What if it isn’t so bad?”⁣
“What if something better happens?”⁣
⁣
This simple reframe helps you shift into thinking about what you actually WANT to happen.⁣
⁣

If you want to make 2024 your best year yet, this post is for you.

The truth is, you really don’t have to do something drastic to create lasting momentum for the year.
 
Most people think that they need to start extreme habits or do things drastically in order to have success. 
 
In actuality, those habits are not realistic and therefore become difficult to master day after day.
 
The key to lasting change is to start small.
 
Whether that’s adding a 15 minute walk to your day, going to the gym, making more time for self care, journaling, or setting boundaries, small changes add up to big results.
 
Why is this? 
 
Small habits are easier to commit to day after day, which is the most important factor in all of this.
 
Change comes from committment. Day after day.
 
When you are able to do something daily, no matter how small, you create lasting change.
 
So for this year, instead of thinking too big, think small.
 
What are ways you can make small changes in your daily life?
 
Identify them and incorporate them into your daily routine.

In a few months, you’ll notice how different you are and how different you feel.💗
